</item><item><title>I don't have anything nice to say, actually</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/B5niwrd</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/0Qjr7cU.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I think sometimes we try to paint people into a box; good people are all good and bad people are all bad. But people who are good and loving and kind to their families sometimes treat people outside of their families like shit. Sometimes, good people - who are otherwise kind and generous - support policies that leave people unhoused, enslaved, disenfranchised, and dying. 

I don't believe in Jesus, but I used to,  and it especially annoys me when these complicated people do. If someone claims Jesus in their beliefs, but I can't see him in their actions, I secretly hope they get to hear it from the horses mouth when they die. I hope they meet the Jesus who told them their wealth would bar them from heaven. I hope they have to answer to a god who told them to sacrifice everything to protect their neighbors and foreigners, as well as their loved ones. 

I know it is a toxic impulse to wish that fate on others. I just don't know how else to express my disappointment. It feels like saying, "l wish Santa Claus WAS real, so he could leave you coal." Is just a weird impulse I have. 

In general, I don't believe in an afterlife; if there is one, I hope it is as precious as this life, or that it is a comfort after the difficulties of this life. Or both, really.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/B5niwrd</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[youngfarty]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fresh(ish) Memes #179</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2rdsXgz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6vlhvq2.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NGqZaHF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/V6nxxxW.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Been trying to play bg3 for months but I'm just too unmotivated.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RseRGmH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O9A1psO.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eHTPT1a.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/LpTJcfB.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/unxemir.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FcSWKWh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SXHtZFG.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kSACyqe.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/z1WEhhj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.